definition.value: A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a hexadecasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl linear hexasaccharide units [linked (1->3) and (1->6)], while to the N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue at the reducing end is linked (1->6) an alpha-L-fucose residue.
Aldehydic parent sugars (polyhydroxy aldehydes H[CH(OH)]nC(=O)H, n >= 2) and their intramolecular hemiacetals.
The S-[(R)-lactoyl] derivative of glutathione. It is an intermediate in the pyruvate metabolism.
An amino disaccharide comprising two N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine residues linked (1->6).

A tetrasaccharide that is alpha-L-fucopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactopyranosyl-beta-D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 of the galactopyranose moiety bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has been glycosylated by a molecule of alpha-L-fucopyranose.
The D-enantiomer of 4-hydroxyphenylglycine. A non-proteinogenic amino acid found in Herpetosiphon aurantiacus.
A polyprenyl glycosyl diphosphate having eleven prenyl units and with beta-D-glucosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine as the glycosyl fragment.
